Reasoning: The paper discusses the algorithm PopRank, which assesses the impact of Facebook pages and users' engagement based on their mutual interactions. This involves analyzing social networks and user behavior, which falls under the sub-categories of social networks (cs.SOC), information retrieval (cs.IR), and cybersecurity (cs.CYBER). Additionally, the paper mentions the quality of pages' informative content, which could fall under the sub-category of multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper's focus on predicting the number of comments and future posts could also fall under the sub-category of social media (cs.SI).
